Title: Bringing Down The Man Who Gave Us HIV
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswldf
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 17 Oct 2018
When Diane Reeve found out her boyfriend was cheating on her, she uncovered a much darker secret – that he’d infected her and other women with HIV. Inge Ginsberg is a 96-year-old Austrian holocaust survivor who has recently made her heavy metal debut. Her incredible life includes working in a spy villa in Italy and writing a hit song for the American singer Dean Martin. Image: Diane Reeve Credit: Alyssa Vincent Photography Show less